text:
{
  "prompt": "A modified electric delivery bicycle parked under a bridge. The original bike has a step-through frame and a large black delivery box on the rear rack. The modified version has a front suspension fork designed for 27.5-inch wheels and a 26-inch spoked front wheel with a thinner tire compared to the rear. The rear wheel remains a 20-inch cast wheel with a thick tire. The front fork is visibly taller and more modern-looking, while the bike still maintains its overall shape and blue color. The background includes stone walls, concrete pillars, and benches under an overpass.",
  "referenced_image_ids": ["file-UBusq9UUo8VMLjskuS5VQM"]
}

{
  "prompt": "An electric delivery bike with a step-through frame, custom-painted in an Andy Warhol-inspired pop art style. The frame is covered in bold, colorful patterns, repeating comic-style prints, vibrant contrasts, and playful iconography similar to Warhol's work. The background is a stone-wall and urban setting under a bridge, with a black delivery bag mounted on the rear rack. The front wheel is slightly larger, giving a forward-leaning stance. The frame still includes Korean characters '춘봉이' painted prominently.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}

{
  "prompt": "A side-view image of an electric bicycle with a white frame base featuring bold Pop Art-inspired geometric patterns in high-contrast primary colors (red, blue, yellow, and black). The patterns are applied in a random but balanced composition across the frame, giving the bicycle a loud, kitschy, Warhol-style art appearance. The background is neutral to highlight the vivid frame design. The bike has a rear delivery rack and black components, with modern wheels and front suspension.",
  "size": "1024x1024"
}
